cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.DS. 

The paper deals with a problem in discrete geometry involving arrangements of lines, which suggests that it belongs to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of topological methods in a previous work and the development of an algorithm also suggest that it could belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the mention of a general framework for solving similar problems suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
